Description: client/server network library for multiplayer games (development files)
 yojimbo is a network library for client/server games with dedicated
 servers: encrypted and authenticated UDP connections (via netcode),
 acks and packet fragmentation (via reliable), reliable-ordered and
 unreliable-unordered message channels over a bitpacked serializer
 (via serialize), and per-client memory silos so one client cannot
 starve another.
 .
 This package contains the static library and the yojimbo headers.

Package: yojimbo
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: libyojimbo-dev (>= ${source:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: client/server network library for multiplayer games (metapackage)
 Convenience metapackage so that `apt install yojimbo` installs the
 yojimbo development files and their dependencies.
 .
 The actual library is in libyojimbo-dev.
